The paper proposes methods for learning vector representations of words and phrases using neural network classifiers, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The focus on sentence context and dependency trees suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of term-matching suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
